
[1]chastisement

   CHASTISEMENT, n. Correction; punishment; pain inflicted for punishment
   and correction, either by stripes or otherwise.

   Shall I so much dishonour my fair stars, On equal terms to give him
   chastisement.

   I have borne chastisement, I will not offend any more. Job 34.

   The chastisement of our peace, in Scripture, was the pain which Christ
   suffered to purchase our peace and reconciliation to God. Is. 53.
